      About this item

      • Stylish and Brilliant Smart Switch: Featuring a full-touch interface, the smart light switch enhances home aesthetic. The built-in LED light can display different lighting effects to suit for your needs.
      • Remote Control via App: Effortlessly connect the smart switches for lights to the eWeLink app and control your home appliances from anywhere. Never worry about leaving with the lights on.
      • Scheduling & Timer: The interruptor inteligente allows you to set schedules and timers according to your needs. You can automate your lighting to turn on at dusk. The smart life light switch makes life more convenient.
      • Voice Control: Enjoy hands-free control with voice commands. The wifi light switch is compatible with Alexa and Google Home, allowing you to control your appliances simply by speaking.
      • Changeable Faceplates: Customize the look of the alexa light switch to match your home's style. The faceplate is replaceable, and you can opt for different themes, such as a cartoon design for a child's room. (Note: Additional themed faceplates of touch switch are sold separately.)

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • RJH
        1.0 out of 5 stars Only works with one App, not UL or ETL approval
        Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
        Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
        I like this unit, but I cannot use it with my current automation system. The unit itself has 4 surface areas that you touch to toggle the load on and off for that area. So, by itself you could use it to just control a bunch of loads. It would be ideal if you could use it as a scene controller and control loads in other areas of the home. If this was Zigbee or Tuya based, then you would be able to do that. As it is, you need to use the EweLink App which I bet most people are not using. Each touch area has an LED under it that glows on the edge when that load is on. You can also specify a default color that is always on under the entire unit. It makes a sound when you turn a load on or off. Unfortunately, you cannot control what sound is played or the volume of the sound. Another issue is that it is not UL or ETL approved which is a safety issue.
